{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place sugar, nutmeg and cardamom into mixing bowl and mill <b>30 sec\/speed 10<b>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add ghee and mix <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add egg yolks, bicarbonate of soda, baking powder, semolina and yoghurt and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour and salt and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>, until consistency of biscuit dough. Form mixture into 35 walnut-size balls (approx. 20 g each). Place onto prepared baking trays, leaving a 3 cm space between balls.","Lightly beat reserved egg whites with a fork. Dip each almond into beaten egg whites and press onto top of each biscuit. Bake for 12-18 minutes (180°C). Transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["170 g raw sugar","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","1 ½ tsp ground cardamom","180 g ghee (see Tips)","2 eggs (separated)","¼ tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 tsp baking powder","60 g semolina","50 g natural yoghurt","350 g plain flour","1 pinch salt","35 blanched almonds"]}],"id":"r132149","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-_UYCeaCJcxg\/XZWrYhyGBHI\/AAAAAAAAfmg\/zLjG92HdLbET63zyDNco5bGL3L8ADtEZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kVp6kn7NDSUk6Dbi.png","title":"Nankhatai (Cardamom biscuits)","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"6.3 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"13.6 g","calories":"498 kJ \/ 118 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own ghee, please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","35m","35 portions"]}